Title: Canonical Quantization of Non-Einsteinian Gravity and the Problem of

TimeAuthors: Peter Schaller and Thomas Strobl

Comments: 20 pages, LaTeX, TUW9213

Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 11 (1994) 331-346

For a 1+1 dimensional theory of gravity with torsion different approaches tothe formulation of a quantum theory are presented. They are shown to lead tothe same finite dimensional quantum system. Conceptual questions of quantumgravity like e.g.\ the problem of time are discussed in this framework.